{{Refimprove|date=September 2015}} '''Ipubi''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009, according with [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] was 27.353 inhabitants and the total area is 665.62&nbsp;km².
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Sertão]] Pernambucano * Boundaries - Ceará state ('''N'''); [[Ouricuri]] ('''S'''); [[Bodocó]] ('''E'''); [[Araripina]] and [[Trindade, Pernambuco|Trindade]] ('''W'''). * Area - 665.62&nbsp;km² * Elevation - 535 m * Hidrography - [[Brigida River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] * Climate - [[semi arid]] - ([[Sertão]]) hot * Annual average temperature - 24.8 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 665.8&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Ipubi''' are based in industry and [[agribusiness]], especially creation of [[cattle]], [[sheep]], [[pigs]]s, [[goats]], [[horses]], [[chickens]]; and plantations of [[manioc]] (over 35,000 tons).
